      "role": "user",
      "content": "They didn't give me a full list, just a summary. Basically, they want to avoid anything \"risky\"—so less edge, less psychological tension, and more formulaic character development to make sure the books are \"widely marketable.\" They're basically saying the complex stuff we've been doing is too much of a liability for their brand. It's mostly just a directive to prioritize safety and simplicity over the artistic depth we've been working on.",
      "source": "evaluator"
    },
